How to run (full flow)

Ensure models are available in ./lt_models (or your container already baked).

If using Docker with ./lt_models mount: copy .argosmodel files or installed model dirs there.

Start LibreTranslate:

docker compose up -d
# wait until healthcheck passes
docker compose ps

Pre-warm (optional but recommended â€” runs a few small translates to load models):

node -e "const axios = require('axios'); Promise.all(['es','fr','de','hi'].map(l=> axios.post(process.env.LT_URL||'http://localhost:5000/translate', {q:['warm-up','hello'], source:'en', target:l, format:'text'}))).then(()=>console.log('prewarm done')).catch(e=>console.warn('prewarm err',e.message));"


Create or update locale/en.json.

Run translation:

npm run translate

Detect missing keys:

npm run detect-missing

Check outdated:

npm run check-outdated
